		<div id="comment_body_64712946">Yep. This. <br> <br>

In other countries, national ID numbers are public knowledge &amp; no proof of anything; They're just a number linked to a specific person, nothing more. <br> <br>

If you want authentication, you need either a govt issued photo ID for in-person or, for online, a digital certificate/encrypted authentication. AFAIK, in the EU this is the norm &amp; they're working on making them interoperable between countries to make it easier to travel &amp; work in different EU member countries.</div>
