	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64713162"><p>SSN Is Not a Form of Identification!</p><p>In the 1930's as Fascism was gaining traction in Europe the US decided to assign everyone a number.  Not to be used for ID, but to give you Social Security benefits.</p><p>1962 the IRS starts using the number to gather tax info.  1969 the military uses the SSN to ID you.  1977 Federal food assistance is using it.</p><p>Now it is your ID, just like they said it wasn't</p></div>
	</div>

